{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_19","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"obo-grep.pl --noheader -r 'term_tracker_item \\\"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/' src/ontology/go-edit.obo | rg -n -C 2 'created_by: mah|creation_date: 2010-10-26|GO:00723'\"","aggregated_output":"191-alt_id: GO:0031576\n192-alt_id: GO:0071779\n193:alt_id: GO:0072395\n194-alt_id: GO:0072404\n195-alt_id: GO:0072407\n--\n3587-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/20253\" xsd:anyURI\n3588-created_by: krc\n3589:creation_date: 2010-10-26T03:56:48Z\n3590-\n3591-[Term]\n--\n29056-namespace: biological_process\n29057-def: \"A protein activation cascade that initiates blood coagulation, triggered when Factor XII, prekallikrein (PK) and high-molecular-weight kininogen  (HK) assemble on a suitable surface or polymer. This results in the reciprocal activation of factor XII to Factor XIIa by kallikrein, and PK to kallikrein by Factor XIIa. The resulting generation of Factor XIIa activates Factor XI to Factor XIa, which then converts Factor IX to Factor IXa. Factor IXa converts Factor X to Xa. Factor Xa then initiates the common pathway.\" [GOC:add, GOC:mah, GOC:pde, PMID:26018600]\n29058:comment: See also the biological process term 'blood coagulation, extrinsic pathway ; GO:0007598' and 'blood coagulation, common pathway ; GO:0072377'.\n29059-synonym: \"initiation of blood coagulation cascade, contact activation system\" EXACT [PMID:18695377]\n29060-synonym: \"initiation of blood coagulation cascade, contact pathway\" EXACT [PMID:26018600]\n29061:is_a: GO:0072376 ! protein activation cascade\n29062:relationship: part_of GO:0072378 ! blood coagulation, fibrin clot formation\n29063-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30501\" xsd:anyURI\n29064-\n--\n29068-namespace: biological_process\n29069-def: \"A protein activation cascade that initiates blood coagulation, starting with a signal from tissue factor (TF), a cell-surface, integral-membrane protein, which converts Factor IX to IXa, and Factor IXa converts Factor X to Xa. Factor Xa then initiates the common pathway.\" [GOC:add, GOC:mah, GOC:pde, PMID:26018600]\n29070:comment: See also the biological process term 'blood coagulation, intrinsic pathway ; GO:0007597' and 'blood coagulation, common pathway ; GO:0072377'.\n29071-synonym: \"initiation of blood coagulation cascade, tissue factor pathway\" EXACT [PMID:26018600]\n29072:is_a: GO:0072376 ! protein activation cascade\n29073:relationship: part_of GO:0072378 ! blood coagulation, fibrin clot formation\n29074-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30501\" xsd:anyURI\n29075-\n--\n31915-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/27278\" xsd:anyURI\n31916-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30193\" xsd:anyURI\n31917:created_by: mah\n31918-creation_date: 2009-09-01T02:25:22Z\n31919-\n--\n40036-namespace: molecular_function\n40037-def: \"OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: zeinoxanthin + NADPH + O2 + H+ = lutein + NADP+ + H2O. Adds a hydroxyl group to the epsilon ring of the alpha-carotene.\" [PMID:8837513]\n40038:comment: This term was obsoleted because it represents a specific substrate of carotene epsilon hydroxylase activity ; GO:0072374\n40039-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28365\" xsd:anyURI\n40040-is_obsolete: true\n40041:replaced_by: GO:0072374\n40042-\n40043-[Term]\n--\n41552-consider: GO:0006357\n41553-consider: GO:0051321\n41554:created_by: mah\n41555-creation_date: 2012-04-20T02:45:12Z\n41556-\n--\n44778-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30193\" xsd:anyURI\n44779-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30815\" xsd:anyURI\n4